59
00:05:30,550 --> 00:05:31,520
It's so cute.

60
00:05:32,430 --> 00:05:33,650
This cat

61
00:05:34,409 --> 00:05:35,670
looks so goofy.

62
00:05:36,730 --> 00:05:37,470
Yes.

63
00:05:38,300 --> 00:05:39,300
Just like you.

64
00:05:39,300 --> 00:05:40,200
Hey!

65
00:05:43,409 --> 00:05:44,200
Wait.

66
00:05:45,340 --> 00:05:49,470
Isn't this one of the capsule toys
from the convenience store where I work?

67
00:05:53,780 --> 00:05:56,030
Have you been secretly
watching me at work?

68
00:05:56,030 --> 00:05:58,030
Who would do something that boring?

69
00:05:59,420 --> 00:06:03,740
[Tea Eggs—NT$9 each]

70
00:06:03,760 --> 00:06:08,680
[Keep scanning for maximum discounts]

71
00:06:05,210 --> 00:06:06,610
You're in a good mood.

72
00:06:06,870 --> 00:06:08,400
Who are you thinking about?

73
00:06:09,050 --> 00:06:10,000
Let me change the water for you.

74
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:10,420
Okay.

75
00:06:10,440 --> 00:06:11,080
Thank you.

76
00:06:13,900 --> 00:06:14,490
Just leave it over there

77
00:06:14,490 --> 00:06:15,540
when you're done.

78
00:06:15,670 --> 00:06:16,070
Okay.

79
00:06:27,330 --> 00:06:29,920
[International Coffee Month]

80
00:06:31,650 --> 00:06:32,720
What do you think

81
00:06:32,850 --> 00:06:34,060
of this place?

82
00:06:47,870 --> 00:06:49,070
You can just sit here.

83
00:06:57,970 --> 00:06:59,180
It's beautiful.

84
00:06:59,710 --> 00:07:00,940
I really like it.

85
00:07:02,190 --> 00:07:03,450
This is my secret base.

86
00:07:04,350 --> 00:07:05,520
Secret base?

87
00:07:08,050 --> 00:07:09,820
My dad used to travel overseas

88
00:07:10,320 --> 00:07:11,630
a lot for work.

89
00:07:13,230 --> 00:07:15,030
Every time he was about to leave,

90
00:07:15,300 --> 00:07:17,430
I'd throw a tantrum and cry my eyes out.

91
00:07:18,580 --> 00:07:20,640
He told me that whenever I missed him,

92
00:07:21,270 --> 00:07:23,540
I should go somewhere I could see the sky.

93
00:07:24,560 --> 00:07:27,010
He'd be under the same sky,
just on the other side of it.

94
00:07:27,010 --> 00:07:29,440
That way, we'd feel a little closer.

95
00:07:29,980 --> 00:07:31,440
Maybe it really does work.

96
00:07:32,210 --> 00:07:33,820
These stars

97
00:07:33,890 --> 00:07:35,950
look just like the ones at your place.

98
00:07:36,780 --> 00:07:38,240
No matter how dark it is,

99
00:07:38,270 --> 00:07:39,970
the stars still shine.

100
00:07:43,960 --> 00:07:45,430
My dad told me that.

101
00:07:46,030 --> 00:07:46,990
No matter how dark it is,

102
00:07:46,990 --> 00:07:48,200
the stars still shine.

103
00:07:48,200 --> 00:07:49,130
Look.

104
00:07:50,330 --> 00:07:51,370
It's so pretty.

105
00:07:51,370 --> 00:07:52,030
Right?

106
00:07:53,270 --> 00:07:55,640
If there is light, there is hope.

107
00:07:56,640 --> 00:07:58,110
Even when you're alone,

108
00:07:58,780 --> 00:08:00,440
you don't have to feel lonely.

109
00:08:01,110 --> 00:08:02,490
No matter how dark it is,

110
00:08:02,880 --> 00:08:04,210
the stars still shine.

111
00:08:10,280 --> 00:08:10,920
Jiayi,

112
00:08:12,750 --> 00:08:14,810
no matter what happens in the future,

113
00:08:15,360 --> 00:08:16,590
I will find you

114
00:08:17,620 --> 00:08:18,790
in the crowd.

115
00:08:22,790 --> 00:08:23,590
Jiayi.

116
00:08:24,100 --> 00:08:24,730
Jiayi.

117
00:08:25,440 --> 00:08:26,240
Jiayi.

118
00:08:27,890 --> 00:08:28,680
Jiayi.

119
00:08:31,400 --> 00:08:32,210
It's okay.

120
00:08:35,870 --> 00:08:36,520
It's okay.

121
00:08:37,929 --> 00:08:38,720
It's okay.

122
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:42,630
It's okay.

123
00:08:59,230 --> 00:09:01,040
Do you know what that star is?

124
00:09:01,570 --> 00:09:03,000
I think

125
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:04,460
it looks kind of like a cat.

126
00:09:05,710 --> 00:09:07,170
You mean goofy, like you?

127
00:09:08,400 --> 00:09:09,070
Hey.

128
00:09:09,710 --> 00:09:11,610
I think it's cute.

129
00:09:12,270 --> 00:09:13,600
Look at its little paws.

130
00:09:40,430 --> 00:09:42,130
Thank you for today.

131
00:09:44,020 --> 00:09:44,720
Go home.

132
00:09:55,960 --> 00:09:57,020
Bye.

133
00:09:57,290 --> 00:09:58,260
Go home.

134
00:09:58,760 --> 00:09:59,530
Bye.

135
00:10:08,280 --> 00:10:10,370
[Gu Yitong]

136
00:10:12,630 --> 00:10:13,390
Hello.

137
00:10:16,050 --> 00:10:16,850
What's wrong?

138
00:10:23,050 --> 00:10:23,850
You know what I heard?

139
00:10:23,850 --> 00:10:25,250
Apparently He and Gu Yitong

140
00:10:25,250 --> 00:10:26,890
have been getting really close lately.

141
00:10:26,890 --> 00:10:28,420
Seriously?

142
00:10:28,420 --> 00:10:29,450
Isn't He

143
00:10:29,600 --> 00:10:31,260
usually not that friendly with girls?

144
00:10:31,260 --> 00:10:32,230
But I saw Gu Yitong

145
00:10:32,230 --> 00:10:33,330
go up to him herself,

146
00:10:33,330 --> 00:10:34,700
and He actually smiled.

147
00:10:34,900 --> 00:10:36,060
He's usually so cold,

148
00:10:36,060 --> 00:10:37,830
but he seemed surprisingly
gentle with her.

149
00:10:37,830 --> 00:10:38,630
One is handsome,

150
00:10:38,630 --> 00:10:39,770
and the other is pretty.

151
00:10:39,770 --> 00:10:41,400
And they're childhood sweethearts.

152
00:10:41,400 --> 00:10:43,440
Don't you think they're a good match?

153
00:10:43,440 --> 00:10:44,340
Yes.

154
00:10:44,340 --> 00:10:46,740
I think they look pretty good
together too.

155
00:10:58,780 --> 00:11:00,290
Diaoqin, I'm leaving.

156
00:11:01,050 --> 00:11:01,700
Junjia.

157
00:11:04,190 --> 00:11:05,150
Have things been okay

158
00:11:05,150 --> 00:11:06,480
between you

159
00:11:06,620 --> 00:11:07,820
and Senior He lately?

160
00:11:08,130 --> 00:11:09,100
Yes.

161
00:11:09,100 --> 00:11:09,900
What's wrong?

162
00:11:14,470 --> 00:11:15,240
By the way,

163
00:11:15,340 --> 00:11:16,870
